-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WARNING   : -Do not change the contents of the file "2DSPGR.DAT" !!!

LIMITATION: - info on symmetry groups not implemented yet
            - overlay of symmetry symbols not implemented yet

FEATURES  : - integrated motif editor/creator
            - PostScript output (color/gray)

              color PS-files : about 1.28 Mbytes large
              gray  PS-files : about  430 kbytes large

START-UP  : - at start the motif defined in the configuration file is 
              loaded so make sure that there is a file with that name
              in the "MOTIF\" directory. 

MOTIF SIZE: - You may paint a motif with a maximum number of
              3000 individual points

MOTIF FILE: - the files in the MOTIF\ directory contain three columns
              with the X, Y coordinates and the color code

OPTION MENU:
              okay         -  accept changes and redraw
              cancel       -  ignore changes
              grid fac.    -  scaling factor for the underlying lattice
              motif fac.   -  scaling factor for the motif size
              left         -  first unit cell on the left  (X-direction)
              right        -  last unit cell on the right  (X-direction)
              top          -  first unit cell on the top   (Y-direction)
              bottom       -  last unit cell on the bottom (Y-direction)

              the default values you can edit in the configuration file
              (system\2dspgr.cfg)

MOTIF EDITOR:

            - the origin is the top left corner
            - click a color on the colorbar to select the drawing color
            - paint your motif
            - use <save> or <save as> and click okay for quitting and
              loading the present motif

LEFT BUTTON BAR:

            - there are three buttons next to each other

             <select spacegroup>  <info, not implemented>  <grid on/off>

REDRAWING : - automatic redrawing only after option menu, otherwise
              you have to click the group button again (for example
              after changing the background color or switching the
              grid on/off)

